<Author>kelynek
<Content>Average Great location, but that's about it. We were given room 105 (please refuse this one if given!) which is tiny double room with bathroom, right next to the reception. As the hotel works 24/7, on the first night we didn't get any sleep as it felt like we were sleeping right at the reception - the noise of people coming, leaving and chatting was awful. the night after we slept better, mainly because we were so knackered. but after that had asked for different room, as our original room had very smelly bathroom - the drain-smell was horrible, had to keep the door shut at all time. breakfast - for 90euros we could do with fresh coffee and normal pastries and some place to sit - forget about that one. Eventually we were moved to bigger room (215) and got some decent sleep. would not recomened and would not stay again. 
