<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Only OK My sister, my boyfriend and I stayed at the Hotel Pelayo in September 2005. We paid 100euros/night for a triple with shower and breakfast was included. It was raining when we first arrived in Barcelona and there was another hotel with a very similar name (though I can't remember it off the top of my head) on the same street. We accidently went there initially - but were redirected to the right place. To get to the reception of the hotel you have to be buzzered into the actual building - it looks like there are about 3 or 4 other business there. Then its up a flight of stairs to the lift, then on the first floor is the reception area - again you need to buzzer in.Pros- our room had a balcony - looking at the floor plan i think its the only room there with a balcony.- location location location! right near placa catalunya and near 2 underground stations- huge roomCons- initial problems when checking in despite me having an emailed confirmation; this was sorted out fairly quickly though (they thought i had booked for a double and not a triple)- initial problems with the toilet - it wasn't flushing - again quickly sorted out when brought to the attention of the staff.Other points worth mentioning:- breakfast consists of a hot drink from an automated machine and packaged pastries. there is no place to eat it really so we took it back to our room.I would stay here again, though only if other places of similar price were unavailable. 
