<Author>SenoraSofia
<Content>Pelayo was good Again, I write my comments as a group leader.We arrived at Hotel Pelayo after five days of high action touring, which started in Madrid. Prior to our arrival, I knew little more than the location of the Hotel Pelayo - in the heart of the city near Plaza Catalu帽a. I had contact via internet with a couple from Barcelona who owned a business near Plaza Catalu帽a. They were not familiar with the Pelayo Hotel and were unable to give me any details about what to expect.It was really a very nice hotel. Not upscale and luxurious in modern sense, but it was very low key and comfortable. Our room was dark, we had a view of a non-descript court yard. Another room within our group had a view of the street below with an opened balcony. That was a very nice extra.The dining area was in the basement. We were served sit down dinners and buffet breakfast. The foods seemed a little too much like food from home, example: mashed potatoes served with what we would consider to be breakfast sausage. Some members of our group opted to pay to eat outside the hotel just to get a sample of the local cuisine.We enjoyed the little lobbies on each floor. The kids sat there and talked while taking a break. They also sat in the basement lobby, perhaps it was a bar area. There they had a birthday party with cake for one of our girls.We were seldom aware of other occupants of this hotel. We ate at preassigned intervals, we seldom saw other occupants in the hallways and lobbies. Perhaps we saw others at the front desk, but it was a very small entrance and front desk and one only saw a very few people.I / We were happily satisfied with our stay at the Pelayo Hotel. 
