<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great location but not a great hotel Hotel Pelayo is in an excellent location right next to Placa de Catalunya, but the highlights stop there.To me it seemed more like a hostel than a hotel as you have to press a buzzer to be let in (day or night). Once inside you then make your way up (stairs or lift) to the reception, which you must again buzz before getting let in. The building itself is shared with one or two other businesses.We didn't get off to the best start as they couldn't find our booking details, but this was soon resolved. Our twin room (114) didn't have the best view as it simply faced the less than appealing courtyard. It was clean an equipped even if not very spacious and a bit dated.Breakfast was included in the price, but we decided to give it a miss and so have no idea what it comprised.Upon checking out we were presented with an incorrect bill for 900+ Euros, which apparently was a bill for a different room altogether. So that was administrative errors on both our arrival and departure.For a 2 star hotel it was just about what you would expect, but at 90 Euros per night I'd rather have spent an extra 20 Euros per night to stay at the 4 star Gallery Hotel (pure heaven by comparison), or even saved money and booked into one of the many seafront hostels which are great value and of similar quality to Hotel Pelayo. 
